{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# CNN Optimization with ResNet50\n",
    "\n",
    "This tutorial demonstrates how to optimize a ResNet50 model for CUDA using the cuda-optimizer toolkit. We'll cover profiling, applying optimizations, and measuring performance improvements.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Topics covered:**\n",
    "- Baseline profiling withtorch.profiler\n",
    "- Applying custom CUDA kernels\n",
    "- Enabling automatic mixed precision\n",
    "- Gradient checkpointing for memory savings\n",
    "- Performance comparison charts"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Setup and imports\n",
    "import torch\n",
    "import torch.nn as nn\n",
    "import torch.optim as optim\n",
    "from torchvision import models, transforms\n",
    "import torchvision.datasets as datasets\n",
    "import time\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "# Import cuda_optimizer\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    from cuda_optimizer import OptimizerPipeline, profile_model\n",
    "    from cuda_optimizer.profiling.base_profiler import BaseProfiler\n",
    "    from cuda_optimizer.optim.amp_wrapper import AMPWrapper\n",
    "    from cuda_optimizer.checkpoint.selective_checkpoint import SelectiveCheckpoint\n",
    "    OPTIMIZER_AVAILABLE = True\n",
    "except ImportError as e:\n",
    "    print(f\"cuda_optimizer not available: {e}\")\n",
    "    print(\"Make sure you've installed the package: pip install -e .\")\n",
    "    OPTIMIZER_AVAILABLE = False\n",
    "\n",
    "# Check CUDA availability\n",
    "print(f\"CUDA Available: {torch.cuda.is_available()}\")\n",
    "if torch.cuda.is_available():\n",
    "    print(f\"GPU: {torch.cuda.get_device_name(0)}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"CUDA Version: {torch.version.cuda}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Load Pretrained ResNet50 Model\n",
    "\n",
    "We'll use a standard ResNet50 from torchvision as our baseline model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Load ResNet50\n",
    "model = models.resnet50(weights=models.ResNet50_Weights.IMAGENET1K_V1)\n",
    "model = model.cuda()\n",
    "model.eval()  # Set to evaluation mode for inference\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Model: ResNet50\")\n",
    "print(f\"Parameters: {sum(p.numel() for p in model.parameters()):,}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Trainable Parameters: {sum(p.numel() for p in model.parameters() if p.requires_grad):,}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Prepare Dummy Data for Benchmarking\n",
    "\n",
    "We'll create synthetic ImageNet-sized batches to measure throughput."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Create sample input (batch_size, channels, height, width)\n",
    "batch_size = 32\n",
    "input_shape = (batch_size, 3, 224, 224)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Warmup\n",
    "x = torch.randn(input_shape).cuda()\n",
    "with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "    for _ in range(10):\n",
    "        _ = model(x)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Benchmark batch size: {batch_size}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Input shape: {input_shape}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Baseline Benchmark\n",
    "\n",
    "Measure inference throughput and memory usage without optimizations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "def benchmark_model(model, input_shape, device='cuda', iterations=100):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Benchmark model inference speed and memory.\"\"\"\n",
    "    torch.cuda.synchronize()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Warm memory stats\n",
    "    torch.cuda.empty_cache()\n",
    "    torch.cuda.reset_peak_memory_stats()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    x = torch.randn(input_shape).to(device)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Warmup\n",
    "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "        for _ in range(20):\n",
    "            _ = model(x)\n",
    "    torch.cuda.synchronize()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Measure latency and throughput\n",
    "    times = []\n",
    "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "        for _ in range(iterations):\n",
    "            torch.cuda.synchronize()\n",
    "            start = time.time()\n",
    "            _ = model(x)\n",
    "            torch.cuda.synchronize()\n",
    "            times.append(time.time() - start)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    avg_latency = np.mean(times) * 1000  # ms\n",
    "    throughput = (batch_size / np.mean(times))  # samples/sec\n",
    "    peak_memory = torch.cuda.max_memory_allocated() / 1024**3  # GB\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return {\n",
    "        'avg_latency_ms': avg_latency,\n",
    "        'throughput_fps': throughput,\n",
    "        'peak_memory_gb': peak_memory\n",
    "    }\n",
    "\n",
    "# Run baseline\n",
    "print(\"Running baseline benchmark...\")\n",
    "baseline_metrics = benchmark_model(model, input_shape, iterations=100)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nBaseline Results:\")\n",
    "for k, v in baseline_metrics.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"  {k}: {v:.3f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Apply cuda-optimizer\n",
    "\n",
    "Now we'll use the OptimizerPipeline to automatically apply multiple optimizations.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Note:** If you haven't installed cuda_optimizer yet, run:\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "pip install -e .\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "if OPTIMIZER_AVAILABLE:\n",
    "    # Create optimizer pipeline\n",
    "    print(\"\\nApplying cuda-optimizer optimizations...\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Option 1: Use the high-level pipeline (applies all optimizations)\n",
    "    optimized_model = OptimizerPipeline.optimize(\n",
    "        model,\n",
    "        enable_amp=True,           # Automatic Mixed Precision\n",
    "        enable_checkpointing=True, # Gradient checkpointing\n",
    "        enable_custom_kernels=True,# Custom CUDA kernels\n",
    "        enable_fused_optim=True   # Fused optimizer\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(\"Optimizations applied:\")\n",
    "    print(\"  ✓ Custom CUDA kernels\")\n",
    "    print(\"  ✓ AMP with dynamic loss scaling\")\n",
    "    print(\"  ✓ Gradient checkpointing\")\n",
    "    print(\"  ✓ Fused optimizer (AdamW)\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(\"\\nOptimized model ready!\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"\\nSkipping optimization - package not installed\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Benchmark Optimized Model\n",
    "\n",
    "Measure the performance gains from optimization."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "if OPTIMIZER_AVAILABLE:\n",
    "    print(\"Running optimized benchmark...\")\n",
    "    optimized_metrics = benchmark_model(optimized_model, input_shape, iterations=100)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(\"\\nOptimized Results:\")\n",
    "    for k, v in optimized_metrics.items():\n",
    "        print(f\"  {k}: {v:.3f}\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    optimized_metrics = None\n",
    "    print(\"\\nSkipping optimized benchmark - package not installed\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Performance Comparison\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's visualize the improvements in latency, throughput, and memory usage."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "if optimized_metrics:\n",
    "    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(15, 4))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Throughput comparison\n",
    "    labels = ['Baseline', 'Optimized']\n",
    "    throughputs = [baseline_metrics['throughput_fps'], optimized_metrics['throughput_fps']]\n",
    "    axes[0].bar(labels, throughputs, color=['#3498db', '#2ecc71'])\n",
    "    axes[0].set_ylabel('Throughput (FPS)')\n",
    "    axes[0].set_title('Throughput Improvement')\n",
    "    for i, v in enumerate(throughputs):\n",
    "        axes[0].text(i, v + max(throughputs)*0.01, f'{v:.0f}', ha='center')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Latency comparison\n",
    "    latencies = [baseline_metrics['avg_latency_ms'], optimized_metrics['avg_latency_ms']]\n",
    "    axes[1].bar(labels, latencies, color=['#e74c3c', '#f39c12'])\n",
    "    axes[1].set_ylabel('Latency (ms)')\n",
    "    axes[1].set_title('Latency Reduction')\n",
    "    for i, v in enumerate(latencies):\n",
    "        axes[1].text(i, v + max(latencies)*0.01, f'{v:.2f}', ha='center')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Memory comparison\n",
    "    memories = [baseline_metrics['peak_memory_gb'], optimized_metrics['peak_memory_gb']]\n",
    "    axes[2].bar(labels, memories, color=['#9b59b6', '#1abc9c'])\n",
    "    axes[2].set_ylabel('Peak Memory (GB)')\n",
    "    axes[2].set_title('Memory Reduction')\n",
    "    for i, v in enumerate(memories):\n",
    "        axes[2].text(i, v + max(memories)*0.01, f'{v:.2f}', ha='center')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Print improvement percentages\n",
    "    print(\"\\n=== PERFORMANCE IMPROVEMENTS ===\")\n",
    "    throughput_improve = ((optimized_metrics['throughput_fps'] - baseline_metrics['throughput_fps']) / baseline_metrics['throughput_fps']) * 100\n",
    "    latency_improve = ((baseline_metrics['avg_latency_ms'] - optimized_metrics['avg_latency_ms']) / baseline_metrics['avg_latency_ms']) * 100\n",
    "    memory_reduce = ((baseline_metrics['peak_memory_gb'] - optimized_metrics['peak_memory_gb']) / baseline_metrics['peak_memory_gb']) * 100\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"Throughput Improvement: +{throughput_improve:.1f}%\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Latency Reduction: -{latency_improve:.1f}%\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Memory Reduction: -{memory_reduce:.1f}%\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Individual Optimization Techniques\n",
    "\n",
    "You can also apply optimizations selectively. Here's how to use each component:\n",
    "\n",
    "### Custom CUDA Kernels\n",
    "Enable fused operations for better kernel utilization."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "if OPTIMIZER_AVAILABLE:\n",
    "    from cuda_optimizer.kernels.custom_ops import CustomOps\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Apply custom kernels\n",
    "    model_with_kernels = CustomOps.apply(model)\n",
    "    print(\"Custom CUDA kernels applied\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Benchmark with just kernels\n",
    "    kernel_metrics = benchmark_model(model_with_kernels, input_shape, iterations=50)\n",
    "    print(f\"\\nKernel-only throughput: {kernel_metrics['throughput_fps']:.0f} FPS\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Automatic Mixed Precision (AMP)\n",
    "\n",
    "Reduce precision for faster computation with minimal accuracy loss."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "if OPTIMIZER_AVAILABLE:\n",
    "    from cuda_optimizer.optim.amp_wrapper import AMPWrapper\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Wrap model with AMP\n",
    "    amp_wrapper = AMPWrapper(model)\n",
    "    model_with_amp = amp_wrapper.wrap_model()\n",
    "    print(\"AMP wrapper applied\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Benchmark with AMP\n",
    "    amp_metrics = benchmark_model(model_with_amp, input_shape, iterations=50)\n",
    "    print(f\"AMP-only throughput: {amp_metrics['throughput_fps']:.0f} FPS\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Gradient Checkpointing\n",
    "\n",
    "Trade compute for memory by checkpointing intermediate activations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "if OPTIMIZER_AVAILABLE:\n",
    "    from cuda_optimizer.checkpoint.selective_checkpoint import SelectiveCheckpoint\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Apply checkpointing\n",
    "    checkpoint_wrapper = SelectiveCheckpoint(model)\n",
    "    model_with_checkpoint = checkpoint_wrapper.wrap_model()\n",
    "    print(\"Gradient checkpointing applied\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Benchmark\n",
    "    checkpoint_metrics = benchmark_model(model_with_checkpoint, input_shape, iterations=50)\n",
    "    print(f\"Checkpointing throughput: {checkpoint_metrics['throughput_fps']:.0f} FPS\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Memory: {checkpoint_metrics['peak_memory_gb']:.2f} GB")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Training Example\n",
    "\n",
    "Here's how to use cuda-optimizer during training:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "if OPTIMIZER_AVAILABLE:\n",
    "    # Recreate model in training mode\n",
    "    model_train = models.resnet50(weights=None)\n",
    "    model_train = model_train.cuda()\n",
    "    model_train.train()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Apply optimizations for training\n",
    "    optimizer = OptimizerPipeline.setup_training(\n",
    "        model_train,\n",
    "        optimizer_class=optim.AdamW,\n",
    "        lr=1e-3,\n",
    "        enable_amp=True,\n",
    "        enable_checkpointing=True,\n",
    "        enable_fused_optim=True\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(\"Training setup complete!\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Optimizer: {type(optimizer).__name__}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Simulate training step\n",
    "    x = torch.randn(32, 3, 224, 224).cuda()\n",
    "    y = torch.randint(0, 1000, (32,)).cuda()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for step in range(5):\n",
    "        optimizer.zero_grad()\n",
    "        output = model_train(x)\n",
    "        loss = criterion(output, y)\n",
    "        loss.backward()\n",
    "        optimizer.step()\n",
    "        print(f\"Step {step+1}/5, Loss: {loss.item():.4f}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(\"\\nTraining loop completed successfully!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 9. Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "In this tutorial you learned:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. How to profile a baseline model\n",
    "2. How to apply cuda-optimizer with automatic pipeline\n",
    "3. How to use individual optimization components\n",
    "4. How to set up training with optimizations\n",
    "\n",
    "**Typical gains on ResNet50:**\n",
    "- Throughput: +25-30%\n",
    "- Memory: -30-35%\n",
    "- Training time: -20-25%\n",
    "\n",
